cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on converting different types of syntactic parses to the latest English Universal Dependencies representation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for improving the conversion accuracy, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of entity types and coreference resolution, which are related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques for evaluating the conversion accuracy, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible sub-category.
